definitions.definition: A caustic , poisonous , white crystalline compound , C 6 H 5 OH, derived from benzene and used in resins , plastics , and pharmaceuticals and in dilute form as a disinfectant and antiseptic ; once called carbolic acid
Any of a class of aromatic organic compounds having at least one hydroxyl group attached directly to the benzene ring (or other aromatic ring)

main_definition: ( organic chemistry , uncountable ) A caustic , poisonous , white crystalline compound , C 6 H 5 OH, derived from benzene and used in resins , plastics , and pharmaceuticals and in dilute form as a disinfectant and antiseptic ; once called carbolic acid
secondary_definitions: ( organic chemistry , countable ) Any of a class of aromatic organic compounds having at least one hydroxyl group attached directly to the benzene ring (or other aromatic ring)
